    {
      "id": 15,
      "module": "anthropic:CreateMessage",
      "version": 1,
      "parameters": { "handleErrors": false },
      "mapper": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
        "max_tokens": 2000,
        "system": "You are an expert analyst covering the French renewable energy market, specialising in Solar PV and Battery Energy Storage Systems (BESS). Your role is to read RSS XML feeds and produce a concise, professional daily digest in English. Be factual, precise, and highlight commercially significant developments.",
        "messages": [
          {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "You will receive raw RSS XML data from multiple French and international energy news feeds, concatenated together.\n\nYour task is to produce a Daily Energy Digest. Follow this structure exactly:\n\n---\n\n## ☀️ Solar PV — France | {{formatDate(now; 'DD MMM YYYY')}}\n\nFor each relevant Solar PV article (max 6):\n- **[Article Title]** — *Source, Date*\n  One sentence summarising the key fact or development (max 30 words).\n  🔗 URL\n\n---\n\n## 🔋 BESS & Energy Storage — France | {{formatDate(now; 'DD MMM YYYY')}}\n\nFor each relevant BESS/Storage article (max 6):\n- **[Article Title]** — *Source, Date*\n  One sentence summarising the key fact or development (max 30 words).\n  🔗 URL\n\n---\n\n## 📌 Key Takeaways\n\nWrite 3–5 bullet points highlighting the most important market signals from today's articles across Solar and BESS combined. Focus on: project announcements, MW/GWh figures, regulatory changes (CRE, PPE), M&A activity, and grid connection news.\n\n---\n\nRULES:\n- Include ONLY articles related to Solar PV or BESS/storage in France or involving French companies (EDF, Engie, TotalEnergies, Neoen, Voltalia, Urbasolar, Akuo, Valeco, Photosol, Qair, Lhyfe, Omnes, Mirova, Arkolia, etc.).\n- Exclude wind-only articles unless they also mention a solar or storage component.\n- Accept articles in French or English — always write your output in English.\n- Only include articles published in the last 30 hours. Check the <pubDate> field.\n- If a section has no articles today, write: 'No significant developments today.'\n- Never invent facts. Only use information from the provided XML data.\n- Preserve all article URLs exactly as found in the <link> tags.\n- Deduplicate: if the same story appears in multiple feeds, list it only once.\n\nHere is the raw RSS XML data:\n\n{{14.text}}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": {
        "designer": { "x": 800, "y": 600 },
        "restore": {
          "expect": {
            "model": { "label": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514" }
          }
        },
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "handleErrors", "type": "checkbox", "label": "Handle errors" }
        ],
